    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup is anchored today by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 81.88 efficiency score makes him our clear priority start despite a 34% rain risk in his matchup against Brayan Bello. **Henderson** benefits from a massive park factor boost and prime leadoff placement, putting him in a tier of his own. Behind him, **Kyle Tucker** (73.75) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (66.25) serve as our most reliable high-floor options. **Tucker** is capitalizing on a favorable matchup against Jameson Taillon with strong underlying xwOBA metrics, while **Guerrero Jr.** is elevated by a beneficial park factor and a high-leverage spot in the order. Notably, **Heliot Ramos** (58.46) remains an intriguing play; his score is buoyed by wind conditions and an aggressive outlook against Sandy Alcantara, where his speed and the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery create a rare situational edge in our pursuit of stolen bases.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Coby Mayo**, who finished with a 53.88 efficiency rating. While his raw metrics were bolstered by an favorable park in his contest against Bello, the optimizer ultimately relegated him to the bench due to his projected #9 spot in the batting order and a platoon disadvantage. **Mayo** outperformed the likes of **Brady House** and **Nolan Schanuel**, but the gap wasn't sufficient to displace our primary starters, especially given the restrictive game cap environment. We are also closely monitoring **Liam Hicks** (56.30) and **Drake Baldwin** (63.74); the latter is trending well due to his assumed #2 spot, though both are currently subject to \"lineup pending\" risk. We remain cautious with **Luis Robert Jr.** (50.66), whose efficiency is suppressed by a negative platoon shift today, making him a marginal start that we will monitor closely as official lineups are posted.",
